9. System Roles Inside Pantheon Terms

The Translation Engine naturally maps onto existing Pantheon functions.
	•	Spider — extracts structure from messy inputs
	•	Mirror — checks ethical and conceptual integrity
	•	Checksum — verifies traceability and consistency
	•	Dragonfly — performs coordinate transforms between representations
	•	Raven — compresses without destroying the core
	•	Badger — controls attention budget and prevents overtranslation
	•	Blacksmith — tests whether the transformed output still satisfies invariants

This means the engine is not separate from the Pantheon.
It is one of the Pantheon’s clearest practical manifestations.

