17. Why This Matters

The deeper value is not file conversion.
It is coordination across minds, tools, and domains.

Humans think in prose, analogy, workflow, and image.
Machines prefer structure, schemas, and constrained syntax.
Teams break when ideas cannot cross those borders cleanly.

A system that preserves meaning while changing substrate becomes more than a converter.

It becomes infrastructure for cognition.

That is the real return to the Shire:
not abstract wonder alone,
but a practical device that helps ordinary work become clearer, faster, and more transferable.

